# {{ project_name }}

React Native 0.76+ cross-platform app rendered from OmniSight SKILL-RN
(P9 #294). React 18 + TypeScript 5 + Hermes + New Architecture
(Fabric + TurboModules). Contrast-pack next to SKILL-FLUTTER.

## Platform targets

| Store         | Profile                                      | Build command                                     |
|---------------|----------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
| App Store     | `configs/platforms/ios-arm64.yaml`           | `npx react-native build-ios --mode=Release`       |
| Google Play   | `configs/platforms/android-arm64-v8a.yaml`   | `npx react-native build-android --mode=Release`   |

- iOS: `Podfile platform :ios, '{{ min_os_version_ios }}'` (StoreKit 2 baseline).
- Android: `minSdk = {{ min_os_version_android }}`, `targetSdk = {{ sdk_version_android }}`, `compileSdk = {{ sdk_version_android }}`.

## Running locally

```sh
npm install
cd ios && pod install && cd ..
npx react-native start         # Metro bundler
npx react-native run-ios       # or run-android
```

## Testing

```sh
npm test                       # Jest unit + @testing-library/react-native
detox test --configuration ios.sim.release       # Detox E2E (iOS)
detox test --configuration android.emu.release   # Detox E2E (Android)
```

The P2 simulate-track `run_rn_tests` runner invokes `detox test`.

## Signing

Never commit keystores, provisioning profiles, or
`google-services.json`. Everything goes through `OMNISIGHT_*` env vars
from `backend/secret_store` (P3 chain).

## Package id

`{{ package_id }}` is shared between iOS `CFBundleIdentifier` and
Android `applicationId` — single knob, both stores. Change via
`render_project(... package_id=...)`.
